---
import ServiceLayout from '@/layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Container from '@/components/ui/Container.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Tile Installation"
  metaTitle="Tile Installation Seattle WA | Floor, Wall & Shower Tile | Best KB Remodeling"
  metaDescription="Expert tile installation in Seattle for floors, walls, backsplashes, and showers. Porcelain, ceramic, natural stone, and mosaic tile. Licensed installers. Free estimates!"
  slug="tile-installation"
  category="bathroom"
  heroImage="/images/service-tile-installation.jpg"
  features={[
    'Floor tile installation (porcelain, ceramic, stone)',
    'Shower wall and floor waterproofing and tiling',
    'Kitchen and bathroom backsplash installation',
    'Large-format tile with lippage-free leveling systems',
    'Custom mosaic and accent patterns',
    'Heated floor tile system integration',
    'Grout color selection and professional sealing',
  ]}
>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <p class="text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Tile is the foundation of beautiful kitchens and bathrooms — it protects surfaces from water, adds texture and visual depth, and sets the design tone for the entire room. Our tile installers are specialists who bring years of dedicated experience to every project, from intricate herringbone patterns in a Craftsman kitchen backsplash to dramatic floor-to-ceiling marble sheets in a modern primary bathroom.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Comprehensive Tile Services
    </h2>
    <p>
      We handle all types of tile installation throughout your home. In bathrooms, we install shower floor and wall tile with meticulous waterproofing using Schluter or Laticrete membrane systems, ensuring your shower remains leak-free for the life of the tile. Bathroom floor tile is set on properly prepared substrates with appropriate slope toward drains, and we offer curbless shower installations for a seamless, accessible design.
    </p>
    <p>
      In kitchens, we install backsplash tile in every style imaginable — from classic 3x6 subway tile to bold geometric patterns, natural stone mosaics, and full-height slab backsplashes. We also install kitchen floor tile, including large-format porcelain planks that replicate the look of hardwood with none of the moisture concerns that Seattle's damp climate creates.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Tile Types We Work With
    </h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Porcelain:</strong> Dense, durable, and available in an astonishing variety of styles, porcelain tile is our most versatile recommendation. Modern digital printing technology allows porcelain to convincingly mimic wood, marble, concrete, and even metal. Its low water absorption rate makes it ideal for wet areas.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Ceramic:</strong> A cost-effective choice for walls and backsplashes, ceramic tile offers vibrant glazes and hand-crafted textures. We carry artisan lines from manufacturers like Fireclay, Heath Ceramics, and Clé, as well as budget-friendly options from Daltile and MSI.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Natural Stone:</strong> Marble, travertine, slate, and limestone bring organic beauty and one-of-a-kind variation to any surface. We educate clients on the unique maintenance requirements of each stone type and apply appropriate sealers during installation to protect your investment.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Glass and Mosaic:</strong> Glass tile creates luminous backsplashes that catch and reflect light. Mosaic sheets — in glass, stone, metal, or mixed materials — allow for intricate patterns and accent features like shower niches and decorative bands.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Our Installation Standards
    </h2>
    <p>
      Proper tile installation is far more than adhering tiles to a wall. We follow Tile Council of North America (TCNA) standards for substrate preparation, mortar coverage, and movement joints. Every shower receives a flood-tested waterproof membrane before tile is set. We use tile leveling systems (Raimondi or Spin Doctor) on all large-format installations to eliminate lippage — the slight height differences between tiles that catch light and create an uneven appearance.
    </p>
    <p>
      Grout selection is another detail we take seriously. We carry sanded and unsanded cementitious grout from Mapei and Laticrete, as well as high-performance epoxy grout for areas requiring maximum stain and moisture resistance. Our installers ensure consistent joint widths using precision spacers and finish every grout line with professional sealer.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Why Choose Our Tile Team
    </h2>
    <p>
      Tile installation is a craft that requires patience, precision, and an artistic eye. Our installers have a minimum of five years of dedicated tile-setting experience, and several hold certifications from the Ceramic Tile Education Foundation (CTEF). We don't subcontract tile work to general laborers — it's far too important to the final result. When you hire Best KB Remodeling for tile, you get true tile professionals who take pride in every cut and every grout line.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <Fragment slot="faq">
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
      <Container>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mb-10 text-center">
            Tile Installation FAQs
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How much does tile installation cost per square foot?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Tile installation labor in Seattle typically runs $8-$18 per square foot for standard floor tile and $10-$25 per square foot for shower and wall tile. Complex patterns, large-format tiles, and natural stone installations are at the higher end. Tile material costs are additional and range from $2-$30+ per square foot depending on the product. We provide complete, all-inclusive pricing in our estimates.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Can you tile over existing tile?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                In some cases, yes — provided the existing tile is firmly bonded, the surface is level, and the additional height won't create problems at transitions and thresholds. However, we generally recommend removing old tile for the best long-term result, especially in wet areas. Removal allows us to inspect and repair the substrate and apply proper waterproofing membranes.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                What size tile is best for small bathrooms?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Larger tiles (12x24 or bigger) actually make small bathrooms appear more spacious because there are fewer grout lines to break up the visual field. A consistent tile from the floor up through the shower walls creates continuity that visually expands the space. We typically recommend a maximum of 2-3 tile types in a small bathroom to keep the design cohesive and uncluttered.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How long does tile installation take?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                A kitchen backsplash typically takes 1-2 days. A bathroom floor takes 2-3 days including substrate prep and grouting. A full shower with wall and floor tile takes 5-7 days, including waterproofing, tile setting, grouting, and curing time. We provide a specific timeline for your project during the consultation.
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Container>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</ServiceLayout>
